The paper presents a new framework for proving query complexity lower bounds for graph problems via reductions from communication complexity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of theoretical computer science (cs.CC) which deals with the study of fundamental computational problems, models of computation, and complexity theory. Additionally, the paper focuses on graph problems, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and graph theory (cs.GT).
